19. Use Container Widget in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter is a basic layout widget used to design and style UI elements.

It can be used to:

Set size (height & width)
Apply color
Add padding and margin
Align child widgets
Add decoration

It is one of the most commonly used widgets in Flutter.

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          height: 150,
          width: 250,
          color: Colors.indigo,
          alignment: Alignment.center,
          padding: EdgeInsets.all(10),
          margin: EdgeInsets.all(20),
          child: Text(
            "This is a Container",
            style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}